answer.body:
Circuit Switching: allocates resources for entire duration of transfer, all data takes the
                        same path; Packet Switching: all data is divided into packets, each packet is routed separately;
                        Message Switching: messages are sent in their entirety, store and forward

International Mobile Station Equipment Identity (IMEI) or equivalent: Unique and permanent ID
                        programmed into phone; Mobile Identification Number (MIN): 10‐digit # derived from the phone #;
                        System Identification Code (SID): unique 5‐digit # that is assigned to each carrier by the FCC

C/A Code (Coarse Aquisition): modulated onto L1 carrier and can be accessed by everyone; P
                        Code (Precise): modulated onto L1 and L2 carriers and can only be accessed by US military;
                        Navigation Message: contains positional and timing data and health of the satellite
